      "message": "Looks good. We\u0027ve got like four implementations of matrix inverse now, which is unfortunate. (But they\u0027re all slightly different...)\n1) SkM44 and SkMatrix have their float versions, but only operate on 3x3 or 4x4\n2) VM code generator has 2x2, 3x3, and 4x4, written in terms of skvm::F32\n3) GLSL generator has the same 2,3,4 code, written as GLSL in strings\n4) This code, which is technically operating on floats, but has to pull them out first.\n\nProbably nothing to do (fusing this and #2 would require templates that would probably be more trouble than it\u0027s worth, and fusing this with #1 would still leave 2x2 by itself). Just an observation.",
